Package: lazytrade
Type: Package
Title: Lazy Trading as sets of R functions to facilitate algorithmic trading
Version: 0.2.6
Author: Vladimir Zhbanko
Maintainer: Vladimir Zhbanko <vladimir.zhbanko@gmail.com>
Description: Package provides sets of functions and methods for algorithmic traders.
    Main goal is to process information within Decision Support System to come up with predictions.
    There are several other utilities such as Dynamic and Adaptive Risk Management using Reinforcement Learning
    and even functions to generate predictions of price changes using Pattern Recognition with Deep Regression Learning.
    Main focus is to Learn Computer and Data Science using Algorithmic Trading.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/vzhomeexperiments/lazytrade
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
Imports:
    dplyr,
    lubridate,
    tidyverse,
    h2o,
    ReinforcementLearning,
    openssl,
    magrittr
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 2.11)
Depends: R (>= 2.10)
